radiographic_examinations.findings: Bibasilar atelectasis, left greater than right. Gallbladder distended with biliary sludge and fragmented stones; gallbladder wall edematous and thickened; trace pericholecystic fluid. No intra or extrahepatic ductal dilatation. Normal liver, spleen, pancreas, adrenals, kidneys, ureters, and bladder. No bowel obstruction or bowel wall thickening. No free fluid or free air in abdomen or pelvis. No lymphadenopathy.
